{# Exchange ASSET-FREEZE request (v0.35).

   A TIME-CRITICAL request asking a centralized exchange to place an
   immediate administrative hold / freeze on identified deposit
   address(es) that received the documented stolen-fund flow, pending
   formal legal process (subpoena / court order / MLAT). Distinct from
   exchange_subpoena_request.html.j2 (a records request) — major CEXes
   freeze deposits on a documented theft trail within hours, so this
   asset-preservation ask is the time-sensitive sibling.

   Uses the VERIFIED-aware contact resolver: when the channel is
   unverified, a prominent banner tells the operator to confirm the
   exchange's current LE freeze channel before sending. Recupero never
   represents an unverified address as the official channel.

   Required Jinja context:
     - case_id, generated_at, incident_date, total_loss_usd
     - victim: {name, jurisdiction}; investigator: {name, organization, email}
     - exchange: {name, legal_name, compliance_email, le_portal_url,
       freeze_capability (yes|limited|no|unknown), freeze_request_channel,
       verified (bool), source}
     - flows: list of OnwardCEXFlow-shaped dicts (as in the subpoena template)
     - total_flow_usd, token_summary, le_engaged, le_reference
#}<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Exchange Freeze Request — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Strictly Private &amp; Confidential</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% if not exchange.verified %}
  <div style="background:#7c2d12;color:#fff;padding:.75rem 1rem;border-radius:6px;margin:0 0 1rem;font-weight:600;line-height:1.4">
    ⚠ UNVERIFIED CONTACT CHANNEL — the freeze / law-enforcement channel shown
    for {{ exchange.name }} has NOT been independently verified by Recupero.
    Confirm {{ exchange.name }}'s current law-enforcement freeze-request channel
    before sending, and do not represent the address below as the official
    channel.
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Exchange Asset-Freeze Request — TIME-CRITICAL</div>
    <h1>{{ exchange.name }}<br/>Asset-Freeze Request</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      On-chain tracing establishes that funds stolen from {{ victim.name }}
      were forwarded to {{ flows|length }} deposit address(es) under
      {{ exchange.name }}'s custody. Because misappropriated funds can be
      withdrawn within minutes, we respectfully request an <strong>immediate
      precautionary hold</strong> on the identified deposit address(es) and
      associated account balances, pending the formal legal process described
      below.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Addressed To</dt>
      <dd>{{ exchange.legal_name or exchange.name }}<span class="secondary">Law-Enforcement / Compliance Team<br/>{{ exchange.le_portal_url or exchange.compliance_email or "[confirm LE channel before sending]" }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Freeze Capability (on file)</dt>
      <dd>{{ exchange.freeze_capability | default("unknown") }}<span class="secondary">{% if exchange.verified %}channel verified{% if exchange.source %} — {{ exchange.source }}{% endif %}{% else %}channel UNVERIFIED — confirm before sending{% endif %}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared By</dt>
      <dd>{{ investigator.name }}<span class="secondary">{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>on behalf of {{ victim.name }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Case Number</dt>
      <dd>{{ case_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    {% if le_reference %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>LE Reference</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ le_reference }}</dd>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Total Flow Value</dt>
      <dd>{{ total_flow_usd }}<span class="secondary">across {{ flows|length }} flow(s)</span></dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<section class="content">

<h2>1. Nature of the Underlying Matter</h2>
<p>
On {{ incident_date }}, {{ victim.name }} ({{ victim.jurisdiction }}) reported
the unauthorized appropriation of digital assets with a reported loss of
approximately {{ total_loss_usd }}.
{% if le_engaged %}
Law enforcement has been engaged in this matter
{% if le_reference %}under reference {{ le_reference }}.{% else %}and is actively investigating.{% endif %}
{% else %}
Engagement with law enforcement is in progress; this request is made to
preserve assets pending that process.
{% endif %}
</p>

<h2>2. On-Chain Evidence of {{ exchange.name }} Receipt</h2>
<p>
Independent on-chain analysis established that the upstream addresses below —
themselves identified as recipients of the misappropriated assets — forwarded
{{ token_summary }} to deposit addresses under {{ exchange.name }}'s custody.
Each transaction is independently verifiable on the public blockchain.
</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Upstream (sender)</th>
      <th>{{ exchange.name }} deposit (receiver)</th>
      <th>Token</th>
      <th class="amount">Total USD</th>
      <th>Transfers</th>
      <th>Period</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for flow in flows %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{% if flow.upstream_explorer_url %}<a href="{{ flow.upstream_explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ flow.upstream_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }}</a>{% else %}<span>{{ flow.upstream_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td class="mono">{% if flow.cex_explorer_url %}<a href="{{ flow.cex_explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ flow.cex_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }}</a>{% else %}<span>{{ flow.cex_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td>{{ flow.token_symbol }}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ flow.flow_usd_value }}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ flow.transfer_count }}</td>
      <td>
        {% if flow.first_flow_at %}
          {{ flow.first_flow_at[:10] }}
          {% if flow.last_flow_at and flow.last_flow_at[:10] != flow.first_flow_at[:10] %} – {{ flow.last_flow_at[:10] }}{% endif %}
        {% else %}—{% endif %}
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>

{# v0.41-audit C3: full untruncated deposit addresses for exact matching
   (doctrine: never truncate addresses in legal docs). The table above
   uses short form for readability; this appendix is authoritative. #}
<p><strong>Full deposit address(es) referenced above</strong> (listed
in full for exact matching against your records):</p>
<ul style="font-family: ui-monospace, 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.85em;">
{% for flow in flows %}
  <li>{{ flow.cex_address }}<span class="secondary"> · upstream {{ flow.upstream_address }} · {{ flow.token_symbol }}</span></li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>

<h2>3. Transaction Hashes (for Verification)</h2>
<ul style="font-family: ui-monospace, 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.85em;">
{% for flow in flows %}
{% for tx in flow.tx_hashes %}
  <li>{{ tx }}<span class="secondary"> · {{ flow.upstream_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }} → {{ flow.cex_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }} · {{ flow.token_symbol }}</span></li>
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
</ul>

<h2>4. Action Requested — Immediate Precautionary Hold</h2>
<p>
For each {{ exchange.name }}-controlled deposit address in section 2, we
respectfully request that your team:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    <strong>Place an immediate administrative hold</strong> on the identified
    deposit address(es) and any associated customer account balance, to the
    extent your platform permits asset preservation pending legal process.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Preserve</strong> all KYC, deposit, conversion, and withdrawal
    records associated with the address(es) and account(s), against the formal
    production request to follow.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Confirm</strong> receipt and the hold status to the contact in
    section 6, including any internal process reference.
  </li>
</ol>
<p class="secondary">
This is a request for voluntary asset preservation, not a court order. Recupero
is an investigation firm, not counsel, and this document is not legal advice.
Formal compelled disclosure / freeze (subpoena, seizure warrant, court order,
or MLAT) will follow through the engaged law-enforcement channel; please advise
the contact below of your jurisdiction's process requirements.
</p>

<h2>5. Use and Confidentiality</h2>
<p>
Any information produced will be used exclusively to investigate and remediate
the underlying theft, shared only with Recupero's investigative counsel and
engaged law enforcement.
</p>

<h2>6. Point of Contact</h2>
<p>
<strong>Investigative counsel:</strong><br/>
{{ investigator.name }}<br/>
{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>
{{ investigator.email }}
</p>
{% if le_engaged and le_reference %}
<p><strong>Engaged law enforcement:</strong><br/>Reference {{ le_reference }} (point of contact available via the investigative counsel above)</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>7. Response Window</h2>
<p>
Given the time-critical nature of asset preservation, we respectfully request
acknowledgement of receipt and confirmation of any hold placed within
<strong>twenty-four (24) hours</strong> where your process permits, with the
formal legal process to follow promptly.
</p>

</section>
</body>
</html>
